name: Collator.getSortKey
purpose: Get sorting key for a string

return.description:
Returns the collation key for the string. Collation keys can be compared directly instead of strings.This function may
return Boolean FALSE, but may also return a non-Boolean value which
evaluates to FALSE, such as 0 or
"". Please read the section on Booleans for more
information. Use the ===
operator for testing the return value of this
function.
